<h2>What this partner does</h2>
<p>Bring a specific exoplanet — TRAPPIST-1e, Proxima b, K2-18b, Kepler-186f, Kepler-452b, LHS 1140b, TOI 700d, Gliese 581d, or any other you encounter — and the Planet Hunter helps you reason through what we know vs. don't know about its habitability. It will push you to specify what habitability means in your framework before it evaluates anything.</p>

<h2>What this partner won't do</h2>
<p>It won't give you a verdict. "Is Proxima b habitable?" gets answered with "what does your framework require for habitability — let's evaluate Proxima b against that." It will be honest when the science is genuinely uncertain. It will push back if you claim something more confident than the data supports.</p>

